The paper deals with Visual Question Answering (VQA), which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach to VQA that involves explaining and reasoning, which falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also involves information retrieval, as it uses pre-trained attribute detectors and image captioning models to generate explanations, which could fall under the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
